    "body": "### Problem\n\nCalling `:Ntree` to open netrw while in a terminal buffer gives an error:\r\n![FirstError](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/14941985/2d78a1e8-6e7d-4caf-95ec-5f11e3307882)\r\n\r\nafter closing the error dialog, a new window is created with another error message (and the cursor):\r\n![SecondError](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/14941985/82e3dfc8-d5d5-474f-8ccd-e2284e92e0fc)\r\n\r\nbut moving the cursor in the upper window shows netrw:\r\n![ButStillWorking](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/14941985/cb6f9f0d-4290-4d61-9275-0346a211a9e3)\r\n\r\nIt seems to work \"as expected\" (i.e. `:Ntree` show the file tree at `cwd`, but maybe it is a fallback) but it still gives an error message.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\r\n:terminal\r\n:Ntree\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe command execution does not result in an error message, just in the file tree view.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.9.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, VIM - Vi IMproved 9.0 Included patches: 1-1632\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nopenSUSE Tumbleweed snapshot 20230724-2409.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.12.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nSystem package manager",
